uctor, both throw runtime exceptions. The configuration lives in AsyncMessageReceiveActionSettings with two key properties: the form class package (required) and an optional ID generator for numbering received messages. There are also cross-references to preserve, including a link to the messaging receive architectural pattern and a reference to the Result.Success class.\n\nNow I'm compiling the search hints across the three sections—the action class and its methods, the request and result types along with their processing steps, and the settings class with its configuration properties and related generator interface. For the documentation URLs, the base is empty, and I don't see any explicit Javadoc references or external links to extract.\n\nSince the base URL is empty, the official_doc_urls array will be empty as well. Now I need to map out the inbound message flow more precisely: parsing the business data area to extract the record, loading the form class by combining the package name with the request ID and \"Form\" suffix, assigning a sequence number using the configured generator, and instantiating the form with the received message data.\n\nThen I execute the prepared SQL statement using the configured package path, request ID, and \"#INSERT_MESSAGE\" operation. If everything succeeds, I return a success result. But I need to account for potential failures—if the form class isn't found on the classpath or if the constructor fails, those will throw runtime exceptions.\n\nNow I'm drafting the markdown sections, starting with the overview that describes this as a typical business action handler for the AsyncMessageReceiveAction class, which implements the messaging receive pattern and persists incoming message data to a specified table.\n\nGenerating markdown table... 業務アクションハンドラクラスを別途作成すること。\n\ns2のハンドラ処理フローでは、往路処理として受信電文の業務データをデフォルトフォーマッタで解析してからフォームクラスをロードし、採番モジュールで連番を取得した上でフォームインスタンスを生成し、対応するSQLリソースのプリペアドステートメントを実行する。復路処理では成功結果を返して終了し、フォームクラスが見つからない場合やコンストラクタ